                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Ti-T targets with 300 keV deuterons.",
                " - The neutron fluence rate of INGLU was about",
                "   (1.1-3.3)E12 n/s4pi",
                " - The neutron fluence rate of CIAE was about",
                "   (0.7-2.0)E10 n/s4pi"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Samples of 20 mm in diameter made from natural plates",
                " of Ag, Nb or oxide powder of Eu and Tb with purity",
                " better than 99%.",
                "They were sandwiched between two 0.03 mm thick Nb",
                " samples."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                " - The irradiation lasted 7.36 hours at INGLU",
                " - The stacked sample groups irradiated at CIAE lasted",
                "   50 hours",
                "After irradiation, the samples were cooled for 2-6",
                " months, the measurements lasted 1-6 days for each",
                " sample, then repeated two or three times."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
